^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at| Now, let us discuss the bidding.  First, if  you play unusual NT, I suggest you only do it with 5/5 or better, not with 5/4 as some people do. The reason for that is, it is an obstructive bid, and if partner can count on you for at least 5 cards in the suit, will know better when to sacrifice. Now, as for my bid.  Technically, because I have 5 clubs, I can safely bid 4 clubs.  And my K of diamonds is a great card as well.  My 3@C bid just says I prefer clubs to diamonds, but your hand keeps getting better the more kia bids, so 4@C was good bid.|
PG| ***** 36 ***** |


nt||cp|8|AT|^B@2
^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at| The reason I did not bid 4 clubs was more tactical than anything else. Usually aggie will be weak, and I don't want to push them into a makeable game.  Had they bid 4 of a major, I would have sacrificed in 5 clubs, but I was willing to let them play 3  of a major, on the theory that they can probably make game.  anne has a very bad hand  and passing is very reasonable.  But she has reason to be worried. She has both a heart fit and spade fit with kia. Had her ace of clubs been in a major suit, I think 4 hearts would have been a reasonable call.|
