nt||cp|8|AT|^B@2
^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at| In real life, 4 hearts probably goes down 1, unless aggie is nice enough to tell kia that she has doubleton Q of spades :). And aggie is too competitive to do that!  But the point is, despite the even distribution of high card points, both sides can make 9 or 10 tricks.  That is the power of double fits.  I have played some hands where both sides can make slam. unusual, but it occurs.|
